        "title": "Our Story",
        "heading_size": "heading-standard",
        "rich_text": "<p><strong>Built with Purpose. Backed by Science.</strong></p><p>Dr. Biss started with a simple belief:</p><p><strong>Everyday care products should be clean, effective, and thoughtfully made.</strong></p><p>Too many products on the market rely on harsh ingredients, empty claims, and<br/>formulas designed more for trends than for real people. We wanted better<br/>products shaped with intention, backed by knowledge, and made for everyday<br/>life.</p><p>That is how Dr. Biss began.</p><p><strong>Where Chemistry Meets Practical Innovation</strong></p><p>Dr. Biss is built on more than just an idea. It is rooted in the mindset of a <strong>chemist </strong>and an <strong>industrial engineer</strong>.</p><p>From chemistry comes a deep understanding of ingredients, formulation, reactions,<br/>and how products interact with the body and environment.</p><p>From industrial engineering comes the discipline of designing products and processes that are practical, efficient, reliable, and built to serve people better.</p><p>That combination shapes everything we do:<br/><br/><strong>science-driven thinking, practical design, and a commitment to quality.</strong></p><p><strong>Why We Started Dr. Biss</strong></p><p>We were frustrated by personal care products that looked appealing but were filled with unnecessary additives, artificial fillers, and ingredients people could not trust.</p><p>We wanted to offer products that reflect a different standard:</p><ul><li>thoughtfully formulated </li><li>carefully selected ingredients </li><li>practical for real daily use </li><li>made with both performance and well-being in mind </li></ul><p>Not overhyped. Not overcomplicated.<br/><br/>Just honest products that do their job well.</p><p><strong>A Better Standard for Everyday Care</strong></p><p>As a chemist, we value what goes into a formula.<br/><br/>As an industrial engineer, we value how that formula becomes a dependable<br/>product people can use every day.</p><p>That means we think about both:</p><ul><li><strong>what a product is made of</strong> </li><li><strong>how well it fits into real life</strong><br/>     </li></ul><p>Dr. Biss is where those two worlds come together.</p>",
